# AutoBot — Automotive AI Agent

This project is an **automotive AI agent** (genre: cars). When extending or modifying this codebase, stay within the automotive domain. Do not change the genre.

## Architecture

AutoBot is an AI **agent**, not a plain system-prompt chatbot. The agent loop lives in `src/agent/runAgent.js` and calls Claude with tool definitions, executes tool calls in a loop, and returns the final answer.

```
User message → runAgent() → Claude (with tools) → tool_use? → execute tools → loop → final text
```

## Key Files

- `src/agent/agentPrompt.js` — Agent system prompt (personality + tool usage instructions)
- `src/agent/runAgent.js` — Agent loop with Anthropic tool-calling API
- `src/agent/tools/` — Tool definitions and executors

## Tools (Automotive Genre)

| Tool | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `web_search` | Search the web for current car prices, news, recalls |
| `web_fetch` | Fetch and read a specific URL |
| `compare_vehicles` | Side-by-side spec comparison from built-in database |
| `estimate_car_payment` | Monthly loan payment calculator |
| `get_maintenance_schedule` | Maintenance intervals by vehicle type and mileage |

## Adding a New Tool

1. Create `src/agent/tools/yourTool.js` with `definition` and `execute` exports
2. Register it in `src/agent/tools/index.js`
3. Add a label in `TOOL_LABELS`
4. Document the tool in the agent prompt (`agentPrompt.js`)
5. Keep it automotive-themed — no off-genre tools

## Converting Chatbot → Agent Checklist

- [ ] Move system prompt to `agentPrompt.js`, add tool usage instructions
- [ ] Create genre-specific tools in `src/agent/tools/`
- [ ] Implement agent loop with tool-calling in `runAgent.js`
- [ ] Update ChatView to use `runAgent()` instead of direct API calls
- [ ] Show tool activity in the UI (typing indicator with tool name)
- [ ] Update HowItWorks page and README

## Conventions

- Tools export `{ definition, execute }` — definition matches Anthropic tool schema
- Tool results are JSON-stringified before sending back to Claude
- Max 10 agent loop iterations to prevent runaway tool calls
- Browser-only: no backend; web tools use CORS proxies (allorigins, DuckDuckGo API)
